main event: A witness saw a strange light about 50 feet over a house, and then saw an object about 50 feet over the road that took off at high speed and then stopped.
interesting points: The witness was walking across Tiger Hill when it started raining, but the rain had stopped by the time he reached the top of the hill.
The witness saw a luminous, oblong object with a cookie-lit-like arrangement on the top that seemed to be rotating and moved towards the ground, striking the witness's shoulder.
Another witness saw an object about 300 feet up and 75-100 feet in front of his car, and noticed his car lights dimming.
The Air Force investigated the sighting but found the information provided was insufficient to come to a specific conclusion.
The tape recording was late in reaching the Air Force due to the retirement of Colonel Gilbert.
sighted object: a strange light and a luminous, oblong object
